2.2. Lc nh, hin th mi qu cam

Th hin nh qua cc khng gian mu khc nhau, ta thy HSV phn bit mu sc v cc b phn kh r rng

In[]:
img_rbg = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
img_hsv = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
img_lab = cv2.cvtColor(img_rbg, cv2.COLOR_RGB2Lab)
img_hls = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HLS)
img_luv = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2Luv)
img_ycrb = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YCrCb)
img_yuv = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YUV)
img_list = [img_rbg, img, img_hsv, img_lab, img_hls, img_luv, img_ycrb, img_yuv]
titles = ["RGB", "BGR", "HSV", "Lab", "HLS", "Luv", "YCrCb", "YUV"]
rows = 2
columns = 4
fig, ax = plt.subplots(rows, columns, figsize = (24,12))
for i in range(columns*rows):
    ax[i // columns, i % columns].imshow(img_list[i])
    ax[i // columns, i % columns].set_title(titles[i])
plt.tight_layout()

img_hsv = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1 , 3, figsize = (12,6))
a = img_hsv[180:200,120:140]
b = img_hsv[100:120,150:170]
marked_img = img_hsv.copy()
marked_img = cv2.rectangle(marked_img, (120, 180), (140,200),(0,255,0))
marked_img = cv2.rectangle(marked_img, (150, 100), (170,120),(0,255,0))
for i in range(3):
    ax[0].imshow(marked_img)
    ax[1].imshow(a)
    ax[2].imshow(b)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
print("a =\n",a)
print("b =\n",b)
